divs: sighting detailssighting report: "my son and i were coming from a pee-wee hockey clinic in phila.. we were driving down spruce st. in phila.,pa. on our way back to the expressway when a very silvery cylinder shaped object caught my eye. it was a beautiful bright sunny saturday morning so there s no mistaking exactly what i saw. it was moving slowly through the sky. it was moving horizontally not vertically. it was a very brilliant silver\metallic color. the sun was reflecting off of it making it really,really shiny. i watched it for a good 15-20 seconds. i had to concentrate on the road. i told my son to look at it. he watched it longer than me. he told me that it was flying slow and the it flew away fast. it was the height that a hellicopter would fly in the sky."
trends: There have been no other sightings in Pennsauken Township
